<subSubSection id="DD5F3DD3C2C268E2441B2BAD3CBD034B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A2DF2EEFA3A3C8DBDC364BE88D6BA088" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="773D6BA87F919A2F426A61693B8BAC47" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="DAB7D21F0567D8FEF0AE3AD1E1B7CEE5" authorityName="Jordaens, Goergen &amp; De Meyer" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Mesembrius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesembrius arcuatus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcuatus">
<emphasis id="BB6FFD31CB6B6BEC677A33F65A6C6DC8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mesembrius arcuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Latin) means bent like a bow and was chosen with reference to the strongly curved metatibia. It is to be treated as an adjective (nominative singular masculine).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
